### Enrollment Management API Tests

### 1. Enroll a student in a course
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "studentId": 1,
  "courseId": 1
}

### 2. Enroll another student in the same course
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "studentId": 2,
  "courseId": 1
}

### 3. Get enrollment by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments/1

### 4. Get all enrollments for a student
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments/student/1?page=0&size=10

### 5. Get all enrollments for a course
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments/course/1?page=0&size=10

### 6. Get enrollments by status (Active)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments/status/Active?page=0&size=10

### 7. Update enrollment (add decimal grade)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "grade": 8.5
}

### 7b. Update enrollment (add another decimal grade)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "grade": 9.2
}

### 7c. Update enrollment (set grade to null)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "grade": null
}

### 7d. Test invalid grade (should fail)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "grade": 11.0
}

### 7e. Test negative grade (should fail)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "grade": -1.0
}

### 8. Drop a course
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments/1/drop

### 9. Get enrollment statistics
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments/stats

### 10. Get lecturer course enrollments
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments/lecturer/1?page=0&size=10

### 11. Test enrollment with non-existent student (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "studentId": 999,
  "courseId": 1
}

### 12. Test enrollment with non-existent course (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "studentId": 1,
  "courseId": 999
}

### 13. Test duplicate enrollment (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "studentId": 1,
  "courseId": 1
}

### 14. Test enrollment with invalid data (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "studentId": -1,
  "courseId": 0
}

### 15. Test getting non-existent enrollment (should fail)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments/999

### 16. Test updating non-existent enrollment (should fail)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments/999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "grade": 8.0
}

### 17. Test dropping non-existent enrollment (should fail)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/enrollments/999/drop
